New Records: Caden Dana became the youngest pitcher in Angels history to win his major league debut at 20 years, 259 days old.
Key Match Events: Taylor Ward hit a leadoff homer in the first inning.
Anthony Rendon provided the go-ahead hit with a two-run single in the fifth.
Luke Raley homered for Seattle in the fourth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Dana expressed pride in the win and its impact on his confidence.
Ron Washington praised Dana's poise and ability to make key pitches.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Caden Dana struck out four and walked four.
The Angels rallied for a 3-2 victory over the Mariners.
Luke Raley's homer was one of six homers for him since August 1st.
